snippet.textDisplay:
This lacks the feel of Penny Dreadful. This feels more like a dick tracy/peaky blinders show with a little black magic mixed in.

Penny Dreadful tread into some dark territory. Not dark as in edgy gothic chic horror but more into the psychological states of the seriously damaged characters. But these broken people still managed to be good people. All of them had horrid acts in their pasts that they tried to forget and move forward to be a better person. That's why I loved that show. This preview shows none of that depth.

I don't know what this new show is, but it looks measurably less interesting than Penny Dreadful.

snippet.textDisplay:
What the fuck is this?! Penny Dreadful was a brilliant exploration of the time and the cultures that spawned the mythologies it explored. I would LOVE to see Hispanic folklore and mythology given the same careful and loving treatment, but that's not what I see here.


What the fuck is Natalie Dormer wearing? Everything in the original series was at least believable as period appropriate. What the hell is that outfit at the end that couldn't possibly exist in 1938?


This series says to me that it's creators don't think that subject matter can stand on it's own the way that Victorian folklore can; so, they need to Jazz it up and sell it by linking to a completely unrelated property. FUCK YOU!


Hispanic culture is rich and deep and fascinating, AND doesn't need this artificial bullshit to hold our attention!

snippet.textDisplay:
Definitely would've preferred a season 4 of the original series, but I think the writers just ran out of steam. I've noticed this with a lot of original series writers, by the third or fourth season they're just writing rubbish - best known for this insane 'jumping the shark' and making a series incomprehensible garbage....'LOST'.


Sometimes even dramas with source material fair as badly - case in point, being Dormer's own 'Game of Thrones'; which, despite having a myriad of books to take from had writers penning a final season that was a total mess often with continuity (we all remember the coffee cup and other instances), yet also with characters making incomprehensible decisions and outcomes nobody saw coming no matter what some people say....


I think 'Westworld' did that as early as season 2 and I'm still betting against a season 3 because the second season was so badly written. If you have an actress like Eva Green who can carry the drama through the dips and troughs in the calibre or writing, then it'll be fine. If you don't - like 'Westworld' (though God knows Thandie Newton gave it her all, but her character wasn't featured as much was pointless compared to the first season, so she lost her chance) -it will be interesting to see if Domer can keep Penny Dreadful v2.0 going or whether it'll end up like Westworld.

snippet.textDisplay:
While it looks somewhat interesting,it looks like they are trying way too hard to make a political statement through the show rather than build an intricate and intriguing plot. Of course, we are only seeing a very small fraction of what is to come.
From my perspective, it feels too bright. The gothic sense or feeling of dread is missing. The period of time feels odd in comparison to what this show should bring. I kindof feel like they should have pushed the timeline back, but use the same culture base. Just reduce the amount of technology. Making it a period piece, just a cultural period piece. It feels like it's too advanced from what a Penny Dreadful should be.
